262
00:11:57,688 --> 00:11:58,718
It's here.

263
00:11:59,188 --> 00:12:00,358
It's starting now.

264
00:12:02,658 --> 00:12:05,628
(Flame-grilled pork tteokgalbi roll)

265
00:12:06,098 --> 00:12:09,768
We mix finely diced onions and scallions into the tteokgalbi...

266
00:12:13,438 --> 00:12:14,768
and grill it once.

267
00:12:17,808 --> 00:12:19,777
We wanted to give...

268
00:12:19,778 --> 00:12:22,578
a slightly smoky flavor that pairs well with beer.

269
00:12:23,178 --> 00:12:26,748
We finish it over charcoal to infuse it with a smoky aroma.

270
00:12:28,618 --> 00:12:30,247
The key element is crispy...

271
00:12:30,248 --> 00:12:32,788
fried spring roll wrapper.

272
00:12:33,828 --> 00:12:35,958
When you bite it, you get that satisfying crunch.

273
00:12:38,998 --> 00:12:41,128
We roll it with rice paper.

274
00:12:42,098 --> 00:12:43,328
When you take a bite,

275
00:12:43,768 --> 00:12:45,798
juicy meat and smoky flavor burst in your mouth.

276
00:12:49,538 --> 00:12:53,038
(Smoky honey mustard sauce)

277
00:12:53,878 --> 00:12:57,618
(Cilantro and fried onions for a hearty serving)

278
00:12:57,818 --> 00:13:00,688
Isn't this black pork inside rice paper?

279
00:13:01,188 --> 00:13:02,218
How much is it?

280
00:13:02,348 --> 00:13:03,688
- It's written up there.
- Five dollars?

281
00:13:03,918 --> 00:13:05,718
- I see.
- It looks tasty.

282
00:13:05,818 --> 00:13:08,288
- We can get one for each person.
- Yes.

283
00:13:08,788 --> 00:13:10,458
A roll? That sounds delicious.

284
00:13:11,628 --> 00:13:13,028
(Whirring)

285
00:13:13,228 --> 00:13:15,568
We got another order.

286
00:13:16,598 --> 00:13:18,298
(Whirring)

287
00:13:18,468 --> 00:13:19,868
We're getting orders now.

288
00:13:21,068 --> 00:13:22,138
It came out immediately.

289
00:13:22,168 --> 00:13:23,708
Of course. Right away.

290
00:13:23,908 --> 00:13:25,238
- Enjoy.
- Hello.

291
00:13:25,878 --> 00:13:27,347
- Did you order?
- Yes.

292
00:13:27,348 --> 00:13:29,708
Make sure to dip it in the sauce.

293
00:13:29,808 --> 00:13:31,248
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

294
00:13:32,278 --> 00:13:33,448
Did you order one?

295
00:13:33,478 --> 00:13:34,717
I ordered two.

296
00:13:34,718 --> 00:13:35,748
- Really?
- Yes.

297
00:13:36,018 --> 00:13:37,188
Thank you so much.

298
00:13:37,588 --> 00:13:39,058
- Thank you.
- Sure.

299
00:13:40,058 --> 00:13:42,658
- See? Word got around...
- Right.

300
00:13:42,758 --> 00:13:44,458
that it's a great value for the price.

301
00:13:44,858 --> 00:13:46,398
Yes, it's only five dollars.

302
00:13:47,128 --> 00:13:49,528
- Isn't it nice?
- I'd eat about ten of these.

303
00:13:50,938 --> 00:13:52,138
It looks delicious.

304
00:13:52,768 --> 00:13:53,908
I love rolls like this.

305
00:13:55,068 --> 00:13:57,237
- Will you eat cilantro at the end?
- Yes.

306
00:13:57,238 --> 00:13:58,608
(After dipping the roll in the sauce)

307
00:14:00,178 --> 00:14:01,647
(Munching)

308
00:14:01,648 --> 00:14:03,378
It has a good sound.

309
00:14:06,148 --> 00:14:08,318
(Crunchy)

310
00:14:08,518 --> 00:14:11,287
Isn't it like a generously filled Vietnamese spring roll...

311
00:14:11,288 --> 00:14:12,288
- with a good texture?
- Yes.

312
00:14:12,958 --> 00:14:16,128
Maybe it's because I like fresh food. I love it.

313
00:14:16,558 --> 00:14:17,827
- Isn't it tteokgalbi?
- It's made with black pork.

314
00:14:17,828 --> 00:14:19,098
It's the best thing I've tasted so far.

315
00:14:19,928 --> 00:14:21,968
- This is a steal. It's so cheap.
- I know.

316
00:14:22,398 --> 00:14:24,038
I was so surprised that it was five dollars.

317
00:14:24,938 --> 00:14:26,168
Jung Ho Young's food is the best.

318
00:14:26,638 --> 00:14:27,807
Since the price is five dollars,

319
00:14:27,808 --> 00:14:29,368
- it's very affordable.
- Yes.

320
00:14:29,938 --> 00:14:32,808
Are we doing okay so far?

321
00:14:32,978 --> 00:14:35,148
Us? We got 23 orders.

322
00:14:35,308 --> 00:14:36,378
Twenty-three?

323
00:14:36,648 --> 00:14:37,748
How about the other team next door?

324
00:14:38,848 --> 00:14:41,418
- They're completely wiped out.
- Really?

325
00:14:42,788 --> 00:14:44,057
(The number of orders at Min's: 4)

326
00:14:44,058 --> 00:14:45,858
Try some. If you don't like it, you don't need to pay.

327
00:14:49,288 --> 00:14:51,258
I was boiling inside.

328
00:14:52,128 --> 00:14:53,758
Once people tasted the sample,

329
00:14:54,298 --> 00:14:55,427
they left.

330
00:14:55,428 --> 00:14:57,768
- After saying that it's good...
- They just left.

331
00:14:58,538 --> 00:15:00,438
This is the full-sized dish. It's five dollars.

332
00:15:01,838 --> 00:15:03,667
For five dollars, it's a good deal.

333
00:15:03,668 --> 00:15:04,838
Isn't it a steal?

334
00:15:05,878 --> 00:15:06,907
Come and buy it.

335
00:15:06,908 --> 00:15:08,108
(Bowing)

336
00:15:09,748 --> 00:15:10,778
It's tasty.

337
00:15:10,948 --> 00:15:12,318
It's just five dollars, so...

338
00:15:12,748 --> 00:15:14,418
You get 1 plate for 5 dollars.

339
00:15:15,118 --> 00:15:16,118
I...

340
00:15:17,018 --> 00:15:18,057
- What is this?
- It's delicious.

341
00:15:18,058 --> 00:15:19,518
This is five dollars.

342
00:15:20,658 --> 00:15:22,988
Two to three can share. Order right now.

343
00:15:23,488 --> 00:15:25,828
You should buy it since you're here. You're just leaving?

344
00:15:26,858 --> 00:15:28,327
Come and order.

345
00:15:28,328 --> 00:15:30,498
(Most customers leave after tasting.)

346
00:15:30,668 --> 00:15:32,867
They'd want to eat a proper meal. It's about time they're hungry.

347
00:15:32,868 --> 00:15:35,368
Our food is for later.

348
00:15:36,168 --> 00:15:37,237
Deep-fried shrimps and deep-fried fishcakes.

349
00:15:37,238 --> 00:15:38,307
They're perfect beer snacks.

350
00:15:38,308 --> 00:15:39,438
Beer snacks.

351
00:15:39,638 --> 00:15:41,678
They should sell this in Part Two.

352
00:15:41,908 --> 00:15:42,908
- Exactly.
- Right?

353
00:15:42,909 --> 00:15:44,618
- Part One is for proper meals.
- Yes, to fill your belly full.

354
00:15:45,618 --> 00:15:46,777
Or shall we buy from Min's?

355
00:15:46,778 --> 00:15:48,248
We're almost done eating.

356
00:15:49,018 --> 00:15:50,188
I don't want to order too early.

357
00:15:51,258 --> 00:15:53,688
I focused on the vibe of the festival,

358
00:15:54,358 --> 00:15:56,688
so that might've been my mistake.

359
00:15:58,528 --> 00:15:59,827
Min Seong, it's overwhelming.

360
00:15:59,828 --> 00:16:01,767
They're lined up next door.

361
00:16:01,768 --> 00:16:02,768
Yes.

362
00:16:02,769 --> 00:16:05,297
(Hohyunghojae's queue)

363
00:16:05,298 --> 00:16:07,767
(We welcome group customers. Open.)

364
00:16:07,768 --> 00:16:10,468
I could clearly see with my own eyes.

365
00:16:11,778 --> 00:16:12,837
Enjoy.

366
00:16:12,838 --> 00:16:13,907
(Hohyunghojae serves the orders nonstop.)

367
00:16:13,908 --> 00:16:15,378
Enjoy.

368
00:16:16,048 --> 00:16:17,618
No, we should be thanking you.

369
00:16:18,678 --> 00:16:21,217
Come and taste for free.

370
00:16:21,218 --> 00:16:23,148
(On the other hand, Min's is failing to gather customers.)

371
00:16:23,418 --> 00:16:26,288
(The gap has widened too much already.)

372
00:16:26,858 --> 00:16:28,528
I think we've sold over 100.

373
00:16:28,828 --> 00:16:29,928
Really?

374
00:16:31,198 --> 00:16:32,358
We have too much left.

375
00:16:32,958 --> 00:16:34,528
- What do we do with all these?
- My question exactly.

376
00:16:35,728 --> 00:16:38,338
We've lost. We've lost the first half.

377
00:16:40,198 --> 00:16:42,068
A meal you can buy with five dollars.

378
00:16:42,408 --> 00:16:44,838
A good meal would've been nice too.

379
00:16:45,778 --> 00:16:48,247
The first half of business has ended.

380
00:16:48,248 --> 00:16:50,447
(In the 1st half, Jung Ho Young wins with 123 dishes sold,)

381
00:16:50,448 --> 00:16:52,618
(and Kim Min Seong loses with 53 dishes sold.)

382
00:16:53,478 --> 00:16:56,787
(The next price match continues.)

383
00:16:56,788 --> 00:16:58,287
(35 dollars)

384
00:16:58,288 --> 00:17:02,228
(Highest price match)

385
00:17:02,628 --> 00:17:04,227
I have no idea what they'll sell at 35 dollars.

386
00:17:04,228 --> 00:17:06,358
- Thirty-five dollars...
- Seriously, what did they prepare?

387
00:17:06,658 --> 00:17:09,968
If I were the customer, I wouldn't buy from them.

388
00:17:10,028 --> 00:17:12,068
Exactly. People wouldn't pay 35 dollars for a dish.

389
00:17:12,768 --> 00:17:14,868
The highest price, 35 dollars.

390
00:17:14,968 --> 00:17:16,537
Thirty-five dollars...

391
00:17:16,538 --> 00:17:18,237
- Not 35 dollars, please.
- Not 35 dollars.

392
00:17:18,238 --> 00:17:19,377
That'll be so hard.

393
00:17:19,378 --> 00:17:21,348
For five-dollar dishes and other dishes,

394
00:17:21,548 --> 00:17:24,178
there's a limit to what you can do, so you can kind of expect the dish.

395
00:17:24,318 --> 00:17:26,418
But 35 dollars isn't easy.

396
00:17:27,078 --> 00:17:28,617
Fourteenth place, Essence And Technique.

397
00:17:28,618 --> 00:17:29,948
(During the opponent selection)

398
00:17:30,188 --> 00:17:31,618
We have no restaurant to pick.

399
00:17:31,988 --> 00:17:34,057
Team Essence And Technique has been...

400
00:17:34,058 --> 00:17:36,087
automatically matched with Team Agungi.

401
00:17:36,088 --> 00:17:37,257
(Kim Ho Yoon and Go Seok Hyun are automatically matched.)

402
00:17:37,258 --> 00:17:39,158
The price the two restaurants will battle on...

403
00:17:41,898 --> 00:17:43,568
(Agungi, Essence And Technique, 35 dollars)

404
00:17:44,398 --> 00:17:46,198
I really wanted to avoid 35 dollars.

405
00:17:46,738 --> 00:17:48,538
- It's 35 dollars.
- Let's go.

406
00:17:49,668 --> 00:17:51,938
Thirty-five dollars feels like too much.

407
00:17:52,708 --> 00:17:55,008
It's sickening.

408
00:17:55,378 --> 00:17:57,478
Please, I just want to avoid 35 dollars.

409
00:17:57,548 --> 00:17:59,247
Ten dollars, fifteen dollars...

410
00:17:59,248 --> 00:18:01,218
We make a lot of good dishes within that range.

411
00:18:01,548 --> 00:18:03,448
We're standing on the edge of a cliff,

412
00:18:03,788 --> 00:18:05,918
and someone is pushing us while we're struggling to hold on.

413
00:18:06,658 --> 00:18:07,958
That's how it feels like.

414
00:18:08,928 --> 00:18:11,097
It's a big game. It'll be most interesting.

415
00:18:11,098 --> 00:18:12,098
(35 dollars, highest price match)

416
00:18:12,428 --> 00:18:17,168
Essence And Technique has two chefs.

417
00:18:17,538 --> 00:18:19,097
They must be more experienced...

418
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:20,938
and knowledgeable in food too.

419
00:18:21,108 --> 00:18:24,538
I think that it gives them the competitive edge.

420
00:18:25,078 --> 00:18:26,907
I was the opening member and the sous-chef...

421
00:18:26,908 --> 00:18:29,648
of the restaurant which is currently a two-star Michelin restaurant.

422
00:18:31,578 --> 00:18:35,088
For me, I participated in the cooking competitions...

423
00:18:35,418 --> 00:18:36,948
in China.

424
00:18:38,358 --> 00:18:40,958
I won over 30 gold medals.

425
00:18:42,088 --> 00:18:45,198
From what I know, out of Korean Chinese cuisine chefs,

426
00:18:45,798 --> 00:18:47,628
I won the most international competitions...

427
00:18:48,228 --> 00:18:49,498
and gold medals.

428
00:18:50,568 --> 00:18:52,798
That's the title I hold.

429
00:18:53,538 --> 00:18:57,068
I'm pretty confident in competitions.

430
00:18:58,108 --> 00:18:59,977
It's hard to find a dish...

431
00:18:59,978 --> 00:19:01,407
which costs 35 dollars at a beer festival.

432
00:19:01,408 --> 00:19:02,508
But rather...

433
00:19:04,078 --> 00:19:05,118
Very nice.

434
00:19:05,678 --> 00:19:08,047
I was praying we'd get 35 dollars.

435
00:19:08,048 --> 00:19:10,887
Because a lot of brands we run sell dishes...

436
00:19:10,888 --> 00:19:12,718
which range from 30 to 40 dollars.

437
00:19:13,058 --> 00:19:14,288
We'd have the upper hand.

438
00:19:14,928 --> 00:19:17,757
Tenderloin steak and seafood boil.

439
00:19:17,758 --> 00:19:20,657
We'll serve them on a sectioned plate.

440
00:19:20,658 --> 00:19:21,868
(Tenderloin steak and seafood boil, 35 dollars)

441
00:19:21,968 --> 00:19:23,667
We cooked the meat twice in a way...

442
00:19:23,668 --> 00:19:25,798
which makes the meat very tender, and I'm very confident in it.

443
00:19:26,398 --> 00:19:28,508
(Steak sauce)

444
00:19:28,868 --> 00:19:30,838
I aged tenderloin to make it tender.

445
00:19:33,078 --> 00:19:36,778
And I made the oil soak into it using a Chinese cuisine skill.

446
00:19:37,108 --> 00:19:40,018
When you boil it at a low temperature,

447
00:19:41,388 --> 00:19:42,888
the meat becomes very soft.

448
00:19:45,218 --> 00:19:47,488
And it's stir-fried using high heat again.

449
00:19:50,558 --> 00:19:53,298
The grain of the meat has changed three times.

450
00:19:57,228 --> 00:19:58,537
(Humming)

451
00:19:58,538 --> 00:19:59,768
It shouldn't be fully cooked inside.

452
00:20:00,198 --> 00:20:01,368
- It's not, right?
- It's so good.

453
00:20:01,708 --> 00:20:02,738
It's delicious.

454
00:20:02,868 --> 00:20:03,938
It's super tender.

455
00:20:05,008 --> 00:20:06,438
As for seafood boil,

456
00:20:06,778 --> 00:20:10,248
it has shrimps, squids, corns, and so on.

457
00:20:10,648 --> 00:20:12,118
It'll look great.

458
00:20:13,048 --> 00:20:16,288
Anyone can tell it's full of high-quality ingredients.

459
00:20:24,558 --> 00:20:25,698
This is amazing.

460
00:20:26,358 --> 00:20:28,798
We need to win this time, so we went completely overboard.

461
00:20:30,868 --> 00:20:31,998
The opponent...

462
00:20:32,738 --> 00:20:33,967
started in the last place and moved up the ranks...

463
00:20:33,968 --> 00:20:35,208
in the last mission.

464
00:20:35,968 --> 00:20:37,268
They're the warriors who turned the tables.

465
00:20:37,508 --> 00:20:40,478
A warrior... We came back from the fire pit.

466
00:20:41,448 --> 00:20:43,148
(During Round 1)

467
00:20:43,808 --> 00:20:46,048
(The lowest rank for lunch sales)

468
00:20:46,218 --> 00:20:48,017
(They started the dinner business in the red.)

469
00:20:48,018 --> 00:20:49,817
(Minus 170 dollars)

470
00:20:49,818 --> 00:20:52,488
(The final restaurant to survive is...)

471
00:20:53,218 --> 00:20:55,187
(They turned the tables and survived by making the highest sales.)

472
00:20:55,188 --> 00:20:57,158
They turned the tables.

473
00:20:57,558 --> 00:21:00,298
That's the charm of doing business,

474
00:21:00,398 --> 00:21:01,898
and the team showed it to us.

475
00:21:02,498 --> 00:21:03,568
So I'm anxious.

476
00:21:08,438 --> 00:21:11,638
The chefs next door sure are different.

477
00:21:12,608 --> 00:21:15,348
I felt kind of intimidated.

478
00:21:17,048 --> 00:21:18,118
But...

479
00:21:18,678 --> 00:21:21,048
will their food sell?

480
00:21:21,448 --> 00:21:22,947
At a beer festival?

481
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:25,158
I did have that kind of thought at the same time.

482
00:21:25,458 --> 00:21:27,488
We prepared hard. Let's enjoy.

483
00:21:28,258 --> 00:21:29,488
We prepared a lot.

484
00:21:30,358 --> 00:21:31,528
In Round Two,

485
00:21:31,658 --> 00:21:34,528
we prepared so hard that we almost vomited blood.

486
00:21:35,898 --> 00:21:37,638
The familiar taste is the scariest.

487
00:21:41,638 --> 00:21:42,868
The dish we've prepared is...

488
00:21:44,738 --> 00:21:48,577
Shanghai butter chicken and Neapolitan crunchy pizza.

489
00:21:48,578 --> 00:21:50,048
(Shanghai butter chicken and Neapolitan pizza, 35 dollars)

490
00:21:50,248 --> 00:21:52,677
What sells the most at festivals...

491
00:21:52,678 --> 00:21:55,248
is always the same, at least at beer festivals.

492
00:21:55,948 --> 00:21:59,158
Unlike other fried chicken,

493
00:21:59,918 --> 00:22:01,627
Shanghai butter chicken is stir-fried using high heat...

494
00:22:01,628 --> 00:22:03,528
with doubanjiang and kkanpung sauce.

495
00:22:10,428 --> 00:22:11,838
After deep-frying it to make it crispy,

496
00:22:11,998 --> 00:22:15,268
stir-fry it speedily in the boiling sauce.

497
00:22:15,668 --> 00:22:19,378
It looks so well-coated that it makes you want to pick it up...

498
00:22:19,808 --> 00:22:21,678
with your fingers.

499
00:22:22,178 --> 00:22:25,818
It should be crispier than average fried chicken.

500
00:22:25,918 --> 00:22:27,277
(Butter)

501
00:22:27,278 --> 00:22:29,018
I hope they recognize it.

502
00:22:29,548 --> 00:22:30,818
It's super crispy.

503
00:22:31,758 --> 00:22:33,288
I'll test it outside.

504
00:22:33,958 --> 00:22:36,827
As for the pizza, we'll make the dough on the spot.

505
00:22:36,828 --> 00:22:38,258
And we'll grill it in the oven.

506
00:22:39,958 --> 00:22:41,098
The key is,

507
00:22:42,498 --> 00:22:43,697
when I opened the oven,

508
00:22:43,698 --> 00:22:47,668
I wanted the customers to see the pizzas coming out of it.

509
00:22:49,338 --> 00:22:51,838
I think it was a good strategy.

510
00:22:52,638 --> 00:22:54,277
(Highest price match with 35 dollars)

511
00:22:54,278 --> 00:22:55,808
(Which dish will customers choose?)

512
00:22:57,878 --> 00:22:58,978
Let's do this.

513
00:22:59,078 --> 00:23:00,178
- Let's do this.
- Let's do this.

514
00:23:00,478 --> 00:23:02,347
(Kim Ho Yoon versus Go Seok Hyun)

515
00:23:02,348 --> 00:23:06,088
(Shanghai butter chicken and Neapolitan crunchy pizza)

516
00:23:08,158 --> 00:23:09,558
I prepared a gong.

517
00:23:10,428 --> 00:23:12,298
I'll strike the gong every time I take the pizzas out of the oven.

518
00:23:13,398 --> 00:23:14,697
(Agungi)

519
00:23:14,698 --> 00:23:15,768
Nice.

520
00:23:16,298 --> 00:23:17,668
I thought that was smart.

521
00:23:18,938 --> 00:23:20,638
You need to attract people's attention.

522
00:23:22,008 --> 00:23:23,308
It'd be nice to put one out...

523
00:23:24,478 --> 00:23:25,708
for the customers to see.

524
00:23:27,808 --> 00:23:30,908
