(First half results)

1043
00:45:28,114 --> 00:45:29,153
(Jung Ho Young: Won, Kim Min Seong: Lost)

1044
00:45:29,154 --> 00:45:31,283
(Kim Ho Yoon: Won, Go Seok Hyun: Lost)

1045
00:45:31,284 --> 00:45:33,384
(Lee Yeon Bok: Won, Kim Kwan Hoon: Lost)

1046
00:45:33,784 --> 00:45:35,954
Break time starts now.

1047
00:45:36,794 --> 00:45:40,523
The 2nd half will start at 7:30pm.

1048
00:45:40,524 --> 00:45:41,994
Please get ready for it.

1049
00:45:42,634 --> 00:45:44,964
Thirty minutes will pass by in a flash.

1050
00:45:45,264 --> 00:45:47,804
You can't order right now. The announcement said so.

1051
00:45:48,204 --> 00:45:50,034
We'll start again at 7:30 p.m.

1052
00:45:50,174 --> 00:45:51,574
The menu for the second half is different.

1053
00:45:51,874 --> 00:45:53,504
Can you all lift your right hand?

1054
00:45:54,644 --> 00:45:55,914
Here's the next song. Let's go.

1055
00:45:56,944 --> 00:46:00,184
(The guest singer, BewhY)

1056
00:46:08,884 --> 00:46:10,594
Do you mind doing this for me?

1057
00:46:10,894 --> 00:46:12,023
- What is it?
- This one is...

1058
00:46:12,024 --> 00:46:13,224
Are those the last two?

1059
00:46:13,724 --> 00:46:14,963
- Which two?
- Wait.

1060
00:46:14,964 --> 00:46:17,093
We need to prepare for the next one.

1061
00:46:17,094 --> 00:46:19,664
Exactly. This isn't the problem right now.

1062
00:46:19,764 --> 00:46:21,334
- My back hurts.
- I can't breathe.

1063
00:46:22,364 --> 00:46:23,674
I miss my mom.

1064
00:46:25,004 --> 00:46:26,104
Wrap them up quickly.

1065
00:46:27,074 --> 00:46:29,104
"Wrap them up quickly?"

1066
00:46:29,514 --> 00:46:30,574
You...

1067
00:46:32,374 --> 00:46:33,884
It's time to prep for the second half.

1068
00:46:35,014 --> 00:46:37,354
What kind of heavy labor is this at my age?

1069
00:46:40,024 --> 00:46:41,153
The next menu is...

1070
00:46:41,154 --> 00:46:43,293
(The next menu for the second half...)

1071
00:46:43,294 --> 00:46:44,654
five-spice jokbal.

1072
00:46:48,264 --> 00:46:52,164
Jokbal needs to be boiled down for almost two hours.

1073
00:46:56,274 --> 00:46:58,074
It's been cooked well.

1074
00:46:59,474 --> 00:47:01,474
Jokbal is taken out, but it shouldn't be touched when it's hot.

1075
00:47:01,644 --> 00:47:04,144
After it's cooled down completely,

1076
00:47:04,714 --> 00:47:06,914
it will have that chewiness.

1077
00:47:08,284 --> 00:47:10,414
Into the prepped cucumbers...

1078
00:47:11,654 --> 00:47:13,223
goes the jokbal.

1079
00:47:13,224 --> 00:47:15,824
(Mix it with jokbal.)

1080
00:47:17,594 --> 00:47:19,964
The delicious jokbal cold salad is complete.

1081
00:47:21,094 --> 00:47:24,133
As he was making jokbal, deep-frying the shrimp was my job.

1082
00:47:24,134 --> 00:47:25,364
(Pineapple cream shrimp with the jokbal cold salad)

1083
00:47:25,734 --> 00:47:27,864
After the peeled medium shrimp are deep-fried,

1084
00:47:28,564 --> 00:47:30,134
the pineapple sauce...

1085
00:47:31,734 --> 00:47:34,843
will be poured on top of the crispy shrimp.

1086
00:47:34,844 --> 00:47:36,674
(House-made ketchup)

1087
00:47:37,714 --> 00:47:40,744
Five-spice jokbal and pineapple cream shrimp.

1088
00:47:42,084 --> 00:47:43,313
I was certain they'd be good.

1089
00:47:43,314 --> 00:47:44,854
(Five-spice jokbal cold salad and pineapple cream shrimp)

1090
00:47:45,014 --> 00:47:46,354
I wasn't all that worried...

1091
00:47:46,624 --> 00:47:49,654
because we were strong in customer ratings.

1092
00:47:49,894 --> 00:47:52,154
We buckled up, hoping to beat them...

1093
00:47:52,524 --> 00:47:53,693
in the second half.

1094
00:47:53,694 --> 00:47:54,694
(There's hope if they win the second half.)

1095
00:47:55,224 --> 00:47:56,934
Win the second half, and it'd be a tie.

1096
00:47:58,034 --> 00:47:59,864
You win if you get the higher customer ratings.

1097
00:48:00,104 --> 00:48:01,334
We'll try to do better in the second half.

1098
00:48:02,334 --> 00:48:03,734
"Let's win by selling lots."

1099
00:48:04,304 --> 00:48:05,504
That's all I could think of.

1100
00:48:11,014 --> 00:48:12,074
The second half...

1101
00:48:12,544 --> 00:48:14,484
of the 1-on-1 same-price battle...

1102
00:48:15,014 --> 00:48:16,984
begins now.

1103
00:48:17,384 --> 00:48:18,414
Just a little bit...

1104
00:48:19,184 --> 00:48:20,383
(Screaming)

1105
00:48:20,384 --> 00:48:22,084
Nice. I feel better about myself.

1106
00:48:23,124 --> 00:48:24,654
Seriously.

1107
00:48:25,354 --> 00:48:26,524
Has it already begun?

1108
00:48:26,794 --> 00:48:28,924
This is bad. We've got nothing ready.

1109
00:48:29,124 --> 00:48:31,294
Nothing for the second half is ready yet.

1110
00:48:31,594 --> 00:48:32,764
Let's hurry.

1111
00:48:33,304 --> 00:48:34,363
We can do it.

1112
00:48:34,364 --> 00:48:36,234
(Everything About Tteokbokki is barely ready for the second half.)

1113
00:48:36,374 --> 00:48:38,274
I had a total mental breakdown.

1114
00:48:39,444 --> 00:48:41,903
(30 minutes before the end of the 1st half)

1115
00:48:41,904 --> 00:48:43,343
- Gimmari.
- It looks good.

1116
00:48:43,344 --> 00:48:47,244
(The customers suddenly rushed in.)

1117
00:48:47,384 --> 00:48:49,784
(Full of customers before they knew it)

1118
00:48:50,054 --> 00:48:51,384
Honestly,

1119
00:48:51,714 --> 00:48:54,584
it was important to give up fast in order to win.

1120
00:48:54,654 --> 00:48:57,124
We had to stop. We weren't ready for the second half.

1121
00:48:57,354 --> 00:48:58,854
We had to get ready.

1122
00:48:59,054 --> 00:49:00,724
But we couldn't cut them off,

1123
00:49:01,364 --> 00:49:02,564
so we just saw it through to the end.

1124
00:49:02,734 --> 00:49:03,734
How tiresome.

1125
00:49:04,564 --> 00:49:05,564
This is tiresome.

1126
00:49:06,364 --> 00:49:07,434
All done.

1127
00:49:08,034 --> 00:49:09,533
Number 1400.

1128
00:49:09,534 --> 00:49:10,604
(The last order of the first half)

1129
00:49:10,774 --> 00:49:13,243
Customers may order now.

1130
00:49:13,244 --> 00:49:14,574
- No.
- This is bad.

1131
00:49:16,274 --> 00:49:18,614
We're starting again. How exciting.

1132
00:49:21,214 --> 00:49:24,184
(A delay in the second half opening)

1133
00:49:24,784 --> 00:49:26,624
To be frank,

1134
00:49:27,184 --> 00:49:29,894
the menu of the second half was our hidden trump card.

1135
00:49:31,324 --> 00:49:32,593
It was something I had in mind to use...

1136
00:49:32,594 --> 00:49:33,864
for a future business venture.

1137
00:49:34,164 --> 00:49:35,594
Jipbultteok.

1138
00:49:36,734 --> 00:49:38,494
(Bringing in the straw)

1139
00:49:39,634 --> 00:49:41,304
We got some really nice straw fire.

1140
00:49:41,864 --> 00:49:43,404
We wanted to make...

1141
00:49:43,774 --> 00:49:46,604
a smoke-filled dish by burning straw.

1142
00:49:47,174 --> 00:49:48,473
We will grill beef brisket.

1143
00:49:48,474 --> 00:49:49,514
(Grilled beef brisket)

1144
00:49:49,644 --> 00:49:50,843
Only when the straw is all burned off...

1145
00:49:50,844 --> 00:49:52,544
do we place the meat inside and close the lid.

1146
00:49:53,944 --> 00:49:55,114
It's cooked with only smoke.

1147
00:50:02,224 --> 00:50:04,694
That changes the aroma of the meat completely.

1148
00:50:06,264 --> 00:50:09,263
We also got rice cake from Wonju, Gangwon Province.

1149
00:50:09,264 --> 00:50:11,894
It was to provide cheese-like rice cake to the customers.

1150
00:50:12,734 --> 00:50:14,634
The rice cake was steamed in a steamer.

1151
00:50:15,834 --> 00:50:16,903
(Adding it into the sauce when it's soft)

1152
00:50:16,904 --> 00:50:18,104
It's practically cheese.

1153
00:50:19,204 --> 00:50:22,444
The rice-based tteok was cooked in a spicy sauce.

1154
00:50:23,074 --> 00:50:26,114
We brought the rice cake so that the customers would be like,

1155
00:50:26,344 --> 00:50:27,983
"I never had such rice cake before!"

1156
00:50:27,984 --> 00:50:29,313
(Soft rice-based tteokbokki)

1157
00:50:29,314 --> 00:50:31,613
Next, a bite-sized snack filled with the ocean.

1158
00:50:31,614 --> 00:50:33,624
Fritters for finger food.

1159
00:50:33,754 --> 00:50:36,523
We prepared a menu that you can enjoy with beer.

1160
00:50:36,524 --> 00:50:38,923
(Jipbultteok and seafood fritters, 20 dollars)

1161
00:50:38,924 --> 00:50:41,164
We weren't ready for the second half at all.

1162
00:50:41,694 --> 00:50:44,634
Even so, our goal was to give it our best.

1163
00:50:45,394 --> 00:50:46,464
How exciting

1164
00:50:47,534 --> 00:50:48,604
How fun

1165
00:50:49,434 --> 00:50:50,834
This is wild and insane

1166
00:50:52,274 --> 00:50:53,304
It's here.

1167
00:50:54,904 --> 00:50:55,943
- What?
- It's here.

1168
00:50:55,944 --> 00:50:57,674
What's here? Did it already start?

1169
00:50:58,674 --> 00:50:59,844
Four.

1170
00:51:00,584 --> 00:51:01,584
Five.

1171
00:51:02,314 --> 00:51:03,614
Six, seven.

1172
00:51:04,154 --> 00:51:05,184
Seven.

1173
00:51:05,614 --> 00:51:06,624
Eight.

1174
00:51:07,024 --> 00:51:08,784
The orders kept coming in.

1175
00:51:09,024 --> 00:51:10,354
Eight for now.

1176
00:51:14,064 --> 00:51:15,794
- Like this?
- Yes.

1177
00:51:16,694 --> 00:51:18,734
- Serve it.
- Number 2942.

1178
00:51:19,394 --> 00:51:20,504
Number 0990.

1179
00:51:21,104 --> 00:51:22,134
Number 9500.

1180
00:51:23,834 --> 00:51:25,004
What's with all these people?

1181
00:51:31,074 --> 00:51:32,814
(Everything About Tteokbokki, BokBok)

1182
00:51:35,284 --> 00:51:37,254
Is this the line for BokBok?

1183
00:51:37,484 --> 00:51:39,454
BokBok? No way. Ordering one is impossible.

1184
00:51:40,724 --> 00:51:42,184
Cream shrimp sounds good.

1185
00:51:42,924 --> 00:51:44,593
The jokbal cold salad sounds good too.

1186
00:51:44,594 --> 00:51:45,624
You're right.

1187
00:51:46,054 --> 00:51:48,164
We have over ten more orders.

1188
00:51:48,664 --> 00:51:50,994
Serve these first, and then deep-fry the shrimp.

1189
00:51:51,934 --> 00:51:55,304
(BokBok)

1190
00:51:56,374 --> 00:51:57,404
This is...

1191
00:51:57,834 --> 00:51:59,004
Seriously?

1192
00:51:59,844 --> 00:52:01,374
The orders are no joke.

1193
00:52:02,744 --> 00:52:04,373
We might have to serve 20 more.

1194
00:52:04,374 --> 00:52:06,184
Is that so? Then...

1195
00:52:06,344 --> 00:52:07,613
(Printing)

1196
00:52:07,614 --> 00:52:09,684
(Shocked)

1197
00:52:12,984 --> 00:52:14,984
When the orders keep coming in like that, I'm scared.

1198
00:52:15,554 --> 00:52:17,854
What if the customers wait endlessly?

1199
00:52:18,654 --> 00:52:19,994
The orders are shocking.

1200
00:52:20,364 --> 00:52:21,464
This is record-breaking.

1201
00:52:23,164 --> 00:52:24,993
(Everything About Tteokbokki, BokBok)

1202
00:52:24,994 --> 00:52:26,933
(Current Revenue)

1203
00:52:26,934 --> 00:52:28,633
(BokBok: 380 dollars)

1204
00:52:28,634 --> 00:52:30,433
(Everything About Tteokbokki: 0 dollars)

1205
00:52:30,434 --> 00:52:31,973
(Everything About Tteokbokki)

1206
00:52:31,974 --> 00:52:33,244
Can we serve the fritters?

1207
00:52:33,504 --> 00:52:35,104
No, not yet.

1208
00:52:35,374 --> 00:52:36,544
- Not one?
- No.

1209
00:52:38,244 --> 00:52:40,514
It's the temperature. The temperature won't go up...

1210
00:52:40,614 --> 00:52:42,014
because of too many fritters.

1211
00:52:42,954 --> 00:52:44,283
(Everything About Tteokbokki)

1212
00:52:44,284 --> 00:52:46,054
We dragged the first half out too much.

1213
00:52:46,824 --> 00:52:47,923
The tteokbokki is done.

1214
00:52:47,924 --> 00:52:49,724
- The oil needs to heat up.
- Got it.

1215
00:52:55,464 --> 00:52:56,694
Are the fritters ready?

1216
00:52:57,134 --> 00:52:58,433
Yes, almost.

1217
00:52:58,434 --> 00:53:00,004
(Deep-frying resumes.)

1218
00:53:03,634 --> 00:53:05,474
Once the fritters are ready, they'll keep flying out.

1219
00:53:06,774 --> 00:53:07,774
For now, the fritters...

1220
00:53:07,775 --> 00:53:09,104
- For now? How many?
- Done.

1221
00:53:09,874 --> 00:53:10,914
A lot.

1222
00:53:11,614 --> 00:53:13,083
You're not the problem. This one is the problem.

1223
00:53:13,084 --> 00:53:15,913
The straw fire... I couldn't even start the straw fire.

1224
00:53:15,914 --> 00:53:16,914
Right.

1225
00:53:17,884 --> 00:53:19,724
This is all too chaotic.

1226
00:53:19,984 --> 00:53:22,184
Really. Such chaos is a first.

1227
00:53:25,124 --> 00:53:26,364
The 30 minutes we lost.

1228
00:53:26,994 --> 00:53:28,224
The 30 minutes we lost.

1229
00:53:28,924 --> 00:53:31,763
(Bummed out about the 30-minute break time)

1230
00:53:31,764 --> 00:53:32,794
What...

1231
00:53:33,464 --> 00:53:34,964
- What can I help you with?
- Sorry?

1232
00:53:35,434 --> 00:53:36,704
What can I help you with?

1233
00:53:37,404 --> 00:53:38,503
I've got some time to spare.

1234
00:53:38,504 --> 00:53:39,604
- You do?
- Yes.

1235
00:53:39,904 --> 00:53:41,603
We should cook on high heat.

1236
00:53:41,604 --> 00:53:43,674
(Mr. Fritters is now on tteokbokki.)

1237
00:53:47,014 --> 00:53:48,343
Look at all the people.

1238
00:53:48,344 --> 00:53:49,713
It's way more than 1,000 people.

1239
00:53:49,714 --> 00:53:51,413
(Everything About Tteokbokki starts selling.)

1240
00:53:51,414 --> 00:53:52,414
(Current Revenue, BokBok: 480 dollars)

1241
00:53:52,415 --> 00:53:53,423
(Everything About Tteokbokki: 40 dollars)

1242
00:53:53,424 --> 00:53:54,424
(BokBok: 560 dollars)

1243
00:53:54,424 --> 00:53:55,424
(Everything About Tteokbokki: 80 dollars)

1244
00:53:55,424 --> 00:53:56,424
(BokBok: 640 dollars)

1245
00:53:56,425 --> 00:53:57,493
(Everything About Tteokbokki: 140 dollars)

1246
00:53:57,494 --> 00:53:58,554
(BokBok: 760 dollars)

1247
00:53:59,224 --> 00:54:00,364
Number 9519!

1248
00:54:00,864 --> 00:54:03,694
What a mess. I'm not sure if we can serve all the orders.

1249
00:54:03,794 --> 00:54:06,663
You know the orders we got?

1250
00:54:06,664 --> 00:54:08,404
Once we clear the orders, we'll be out of ingredients.

1251
00:54:09,104 --> 00:54:13,274
We set our budget so tight for ingredients...

1252
00:54:13,604 --> 00:54:16,744
that it seemed we didn't have enough ingredients.

1253
00:54:17,514 --> 00:54:19,143
(Checking the list of ingredients)

1254
00:54:19,144 --> 00:54:21,413
They bought the abalones at a very high price.

1255
00:54:21,414 --> 00:54:22,984
(Abalone: 108 dollars)

1256
00:54:23,284 --> 00:54:24,454
And the shrimp are expensive too.

1257
00:54:25,014 --> 00:54:26,283
To be honest, I was really surprised.

1258
00:54:26,284 --> 00:54:27,624
I didn't realize...

1259
00:54:27,884 --> 00:54:30,323
they could focus so heavily on raw ingredients alone.

1260
00:54:30,324 --> 00:54:32,823
In our case, we used a lot of sauces,

1261
00:54:32,824 --> 00:54:34,663
so our ingredient costs were high in those items.

1262
00:54:34,664 --> 00:54:36,164
(Everything About Tteokbokki prepared ingredients in bulk.)

1263
00:54:36,224 --> 00:54:38,693
It's because you're making high-quality dishes, right?

1264
00:54:38,694 --> 00:54:40,703
Like I said earlier,

1265
00:54:40,704 --> 00:54:42,234
we couldn't prepare much.

1266
00:54:43,034 --> 00:54:46,173
We worried about the lack of ingredients the whole time.

1267
00:54:46,174 --> 00:54:49,074
(They are already almost out of ingredients.)

1268
00:54:49,344 --> 00:54:51,674
Is there any left besides what's on the tray?

1269
00:54:51,914 --> 00:54:53,613
There's a little bit more here.

1270
00:54:53,614 --> 00:54:54,644
We have more?

1271
00:54:54,814 --> 00:54:57,183
I think we can serve about ten more portions.

1272
00:54:57,184 --> 00:54:58,653
Darn it. Ten isn't enough.

1273
00:54:58,654 --> 00:54:59,954
That's even close.

1274
00:55:00,654 --> 00:55:02,424
(Checking the situation outside)

1275
00:55:02,654 --> 00:55:05,224
(Customers are continuing to place orders.)

1276
00:55:05,494 --> 00:55:07,294
I think we should stop taking orders for now.

1277
00:55:09,764 --> 00:55:12,894
Could you stop the kiosk? Stop it for the moment.

1278
00:55:15,464 --> 00:55:17,073
Please hold off on taking orders for now.

1279
00:55:17,074 --> 00:55:18,273
(Current Revenue, BokBok: 840 dollars)

1280
00:55:18,274 --> 00:55:21,003
(Orders Paused)

1281
00:55:21,004 --> 00:55:23,614
Tongs.

1282
00:55:24,414 --> 00:55:25,644
Tissues.

1283
00:55:26,144 --> 00:55:27,244
Kitchen towels.

1284
00:55:27,914 --> 00:55:30,514
We wanted to get the food as soon as possible...

1285
00:55:31,014 --> 00:55:32,284
and serve it quickly.

1286
00:55:35,354 --> 00:55:36,494
Is this enough?

1287
00:55:36,554 --> 00:55:37,853
That's a lot. Good.

1288
00:55:37,854 --> 00:55:39,054
Number 3390.

1289
00:55:40,494 --> 00:55:42,424
Please enjoy it. The tteokbokki may be spicier than you think.

1290
00:55:43,234 --> 00:55:45,293
Yes. Here's your food. Please enjoy it.

1291
00:55:45,294 --> 00:55:46,603
The tteokbokki may be spicier than you think.

1292
00:55:46,604 --> 00:55:49,363
Number 7823. Here's your food. Please enjoy it.

1293
00:55:49,364 --> 00:55:52,373
Number 2557.

1294
00:55:52,374 --> 00:55:54,303
- Yes. It's quite spicy.
- It was so hectic.

1295
00:55:54,304 --> 00:55:56,344
Even the cooking order kept changing on the spot.

1296
00:55:57,444 --> 00:56:01,013
Nothing went according to the plan we made,

1297
00:56:01,014 --> 00:56:02,244
